4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT PROVIDING THAT THE CRIME OF ENDANGERING THE
5 WELFARE OF CHILDREN INCLUDES EXPOSING A CHILD TO THE PRODUCTION OR MANUFACTURE OF
6 FENTANYL, HEROIN, AND COCAINE AND ALLOWING A CHILD TO BE EXPOSED TO FENTANYL,
7 HEROIN, AND COCAINE; AND AMENDING SECTION 45-5-622, MCA.”
8
9 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
10
11 Section 1. Section 45-5-622, MCA, is amended to read:
12 "45-5-622. Endangering welfare of children. (1) (a) A parent, guardian, or other person supervising
13 the welfare of a child less than 18 years old commits the offense of endangering the welfare of children if the
14 parent, guardian, or other person knowingly endangers the child's welfare by violating a duty of care, protection,
15 or support.
16 (b) A parent or guardian of a child does not violate a duty of care, protection, or support by
17 permitting the child to engage in independent activities consistent with the child's intellectual, emotional, and
18 physical maturity, including:
19 (i) traveling to and from school by walking, running, bicycling, public transit, or other means;
20 (ii) traveling to and from nearby commercial or recreational facilities;
21 (iii) engaging in outdoor play;
22 (iv) remaining for less than 15 minutes in a vehicle if the temperature inside the vehicle is not or will
23 not become dangerously hot or cold;
24 (v) remaining at home if the parent or guardian:
25 (A) returns home the same day on which the parent or guardian gives the child permission to
26 remain at home;
27 (B) makes provisions for the child to contact the parent or guardian; and
28 (C) makes provisions for any reasonably foreseeable emergency.
